Studies involving HIV will not be included in this article because different aspects of the relationship between HIV and CCR5/CCR5Δ32 are well established and have already been intensely explored in different reviews (
 Allen et al., 2018; 
 Brelot and Chakrabarti, 2018; 
 Ndung’u et al., 2019). Also, the impacts of CCR5 and CCR5Δ32 on tick-borne encephalitis virus (TBEV) infection will not be addressed in this article because our group has recently reviewed these topics in a recent publication (
 Ellwanger and Chies, 2019a).
